title: Trio of co-starters at quarterbacks highlights Maryland depth chart
text:
Trio of co-starters at quarterbacks highlights Maryland depth chart 
Photos of the Maryland football team during the 2015 season. Daniel Gallen Contact Reporter QBs Daxx Garman, Perry Hills & Caleb Rowe all listed as co-starters for Maryland. 
Daxx Garman, Perry Hills and Caleb Rowe were listed as co-starters at quarterback on the depth chart released by Maryland ahead of Saturday’s matchup at No. 1 Ohio State. 
“Everybody’s in play there,” coach Randy Edsall said Sunday. He also said the starter could be a gametime decision . 
Rowe, who has started the past three games, was benched in the second half of Maryland’s 28-0 loss to Michigan for the second straight week. He’s thrown a Football Bowl Subdivision-high 12 interceptions and completed 44 percent of his passes this season. 
Hills won the job out of camp and started the first two games. He was 27 of 51 for 306 yards, four touchdowns and two interceptions before he was replaced by Rowe. 
Garman, the Oklahoma State transfer, has struggled in his two relief appearances of Rowe. He’s 6 of 18 for 115 yards, a touchdown and an interception. 
The Terps are currently 33-point underdogs against the reigning national champion Buckeyes, according to VegasInsider.com .
